.\" Manpage for simple_shell
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2025" "v0.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [ "command" ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic Unix command line interpreter that reads commands from standard input, executes them, and displays the output.
It supports running binaries from the system PATH or directly from their full path.
.SH FEATURES
.TP
Handles command lines with arguments.
.TP
Supports the built-in
.B exit
command to quit the shell.
.TP
Trims extra whitespace and handles empty input lines.
.SH USAGE
Run the shell by executing:
.RS
$ ./hsh
.RE
Then type commands as you would in a regular shell:
.RS
$ ls -l
$ /bin/ls /var
$ exit
.RE
